To explain the differential equation, we consider a pre-specified value of sensitivity sj. In the differential equation, we assume that both the growth and death terms will depend on sensitivity to treatment, and that the individual cell subpopulations do not compete with each other for space or resources. Hence, the equation describing cell density over time for a population that has sensitivity level sj is given by:6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
